diff --git a/.changeset/agent-platform-catalog.md b/.changeset/agent-platform-catalog.md
deleted file mode 100644
index e27110944..000000000
--- a/.changeset/agent-platform-catalog.md
+++ /dev/null
@@ -1,5 +0,0 @@
----
-"@mcpjam/inspector": minor
----
-
-The mcpjam-agent MCP server now exposes the full platform catalog — eval, chatbox, and project tools plus live MCP server operations — advertises the `io.modelcontextprotocol/ui` capability, and connects the platform MCP server for native widget rendering.
diff --git a/.changeset/cli-tunnel-command.md b/.changeset/cli-tunnel-command.md
deleted file mode 100644
index e8d5dcbb2..000000000
--- a/.changeset/cli-tunnel-command.md
+++ /dev/null
@@ -1,6 +0,0 @@
----
-"@mcpjam/sdk": minor
-"@mcpjam/cli": minor
----
-
-Add MCPJam tunnels to the platform surface and CLI. The SDK gains `createTunnel`/`closeTunnel` on `PlatformApiClient` plus the `create_tunnel`/`close_tunnel` operations (`@mcpjam/sdk/platform`); the CLI gains `mcpjam tunnel`, which exposes a local MCP server (HTTP URL or stdio command) through a public MCPJam tunnel URL and registers it as a server in your hosted project. The CLI's tunnel command requires this SDK version's platform exports, so the two release together.
diff --git a/.changeset/computer-use-expansion.md b/.changeset/computer-use-expansion.md
deleted file mode 100644
index 3cf8061f4..000000000
--- a/.changeset/computer-use-expansion.md
+++ /dev/null
@@ -1,5 +0,0 @@
----
-"@mcpjam/inspector": minor
----
-
-Computer Use grows up: evals accept any vision + tool-calling model (not just a hardcoded allowlist), computers delegate to a remote data plane so credential-less inspectors can still drive sessions, synthetic sessions run through the same eval browser pipeline (render observations + Computer Use), and the computer terminal gets a themed UI with a toolbar and clipboard support.
